name: Ahmed
text: I typically try to avoid corporate / chain restaurants as much as possible, but I can't seem to do that with D'Angelos. Everything there tastes fresh, good portions, bread is excellent, and it's all fairly priced. I've never been disappointed eating there; I always leave happy.

name: Colin Dunn
text: Terrible staff, often messes up orders, or forgets them completely.  Sandwiches are made poorly.  I drive to a further one to avoid this mis-managed mess.

name: Beverly McNulty
text: All the ingredients on my sandwich were extremely fresh. Fresh bread. Lots of filling in the sandwiches. Reasonably priced. Yum!

name: Donnell Hamilton
text: Professional friendly clean establishment. Well done.

text: i got food poisoning here but i will come again it tasted good

name: Katie Furey
text: Deangelos in Braintree served the worst sandwiches.  I ordered 3 steak and cheese and all 3 were burnt with very little steak. Deangelos in Randolph is the best location for fresh and unburnt sandwiches!

name: Greg DeCristofaro
text: Very sloppy sandwich even though they really skimped on the veggies. The roll (multi grain) was tough and chewy. The sandwich was kind of small for the price. The place was clean and the staff was friendly enough.
